A Super Cow is an elite version of the cow. If on a Slayer assignment, a Super Cow is guaranteed to spawn; otherwise, elite monsters have a spawn rate of 1 in 1,000.[disputed – discuss] Elite spawn rates can be further increased with the use of fellstalk incense sticks.

Using a meat tenderiser on it will complete the Beating Your Meat achievement.

Update history[edit | edit source]

This information has been compiled as part of the update history project. Some updates may not be included – see here for how to help out!
  • patch 12 February 2024 (Update):
    • Rebalanced several low level monsters that were harder to kill than intended
  • hidden 2 September 2019 (Update):
    • Super Cows have been graphically updated.
  • update 27 July 2015 (Update):
    • Added to game.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • When asked to create an origin for the super cow on the spot, Mod Osborne jokingly stated that it was created from a normal cow eating some leaves of Brassica Prime.[1]
  • The Super Cow has a unique name and lacks the common prefixes and suffixes of other elite monsters.
